claim.claim-text:
Compressor device that is at least provided with:
- a screw compressor (2) with a compression chamber (3) that is formed by a compression housing (4), in which a pair of meshed compressor rotors (5,6) in the form of a screw are rotatably mounted;
- a drive motor (10) that is provided with a motor chamber (12) formed by a motor housing (11), in which a motor shaft (13) is rotatably mounted that drives at least one of the aforementioned two compressor rotors (5,6);
- an inlet (24) to the screw compressor (2) for the supply of air;
- an outlet (26) to the screw compressor (2) for the discharge of compressed air, and which is connected to a pressure vessel (32) via an outlet pipe (31);
- an air outlet (34) on the pressure vessel (32) for the supply of compressed air from the pressure vessel (32) to a consumer;
- a control system (30) for controlling one or more liquid or gas flows in the compressor device (1); said control system (30) being provided with:
 an inlet valve (29) on the inlet (24) of the screw compressor (2) ; and,
 a tap or valve (36) to close and open the air outlet (34) of the pressure vessel (32);
- a fluid (45), provided within the screw compressor (2), with which both the drive motor (10) and the compressor rotors (5,6) are cooled and lubricated;
- whereby during the operation of the screw compressor (2), or when air is drawn off from the pressure vessel (32) by a consumer in the outlet pipe (31), a mixture of air and the aforementioned fluid (45) flows;
- whereby said fluid (45) is an oil and the pressure vessel (32) is being provided with an oil separator (33) such that, when the aforementioned mixture flows, it separates the mixture into two flows, on the one hand a flow of compressed air via the air outlet (34) of the pressure vessel (32) and on the other hand a flow of oil (45) via a separate oil outlet (39) on the pressure vessel (32);

characterised in that:
- the compression housing (4) and the motor housing (11) are connected directly to one another to form a compressor housing (47), whereby the motor chamber (12) and the compression chamber (3) are not sealed off from one another;
- the outlet pipe (31) between the pressure vessel (32) and the screw compressor (2) is free of closing means in order to enable a flow through the outlet pipe (31) in both directions; and
- an oil return pipe (40) is provided at the oil outlet (39) of the pressure vessel (32), which is connected to the screw compressor (2) for the reinjection of oil (45).
